  fiber: 15 g
  sodium: 1660 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/yucatan-style-turkey-cauliflower-bowls-636afbfd9001cc70ed0c2dab
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce. Drain @pineapple{4%oz}, reserving juice. Halve @orange{1}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Cut @cauliflower florets{10%oz} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Drain @black beans{1}.

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @Tex-Mex paste{1}, drained pineapple, half the @paprika{1%tsp} (you'll use the rest later), juice from whole orange, and juice from half the lime. Stir in cauliflower until thoroughly coated; set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%tsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{20-30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/4 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%oz} and season with salt and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

While rice cooks, in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine onion, juice from remaining lime, 2 tsp water, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, and @salt{1/4%tsp} (use 3 tsp water, 1/2 tsp sugar, and 1/2 tsp salt for 4 servings). Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{30-35%seconds}.

Stir pickled onions; cover again with plastic wrap and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add cauliflower mixture in a single layer and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and liquid has absorbed, ~{4-6%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat. Transfer cauliflower to a plate; cover to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

> Use pan used for beef or turkey here.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add beans and remaining paprika. Cook, stirring, until fragrant and warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, add @vegan chipotle mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and half the pineapple juice (all for 4 servings) to a #small bowl{}; stir to combine. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

When rice is done, stir bean mixture and lime zest into pot; taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice and beans between #bowls{}. Top with cauliflower and pickled onion (draining first). Drizzle with chipotle pineapple mayo and garnish with scallion greens. Serve.

> Layer beef or turkey over rice and beans.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.